questions.title: How would you characterize your skin?

choices.label: Combination (oily skin along the T-zone, dryer skin around the cheeks, some blackheads, enlarged pores around the T-Zone)
Dry (dull complexion, flaky skin, fine pores)
Normal (fine pores, smooth texture, no blemishes)
Oily (enlarged pores, shiny complexion, blackheads, whiteheads, acne, blemishes)
Sensitive (prone to itching and irritation; symptoms include redness, dryness, scaling, bumps)

questions.description: If you have any medical conditions not listed, please select 'Other' and list them. Even if they are in the past, certain conditions can complicate diagnosis, increase risks, or change the recommended treatments so it is critical the medical provider knows your full history.
